On Sat, 22 Jul 2006, Robt Mann wrote:

> As no spare belt came with my '73 bus, I just
> bought on a 50g gamble at a church fair a Gates
> 10 x 890.  I take this to mean the contour length
> is 10 mm less than the designated 900 and the
> section is 0.5 mm (a small amount, no?) bigger;
> so do these figures imply that even with numerous
> washers removed this belt still won't fit?
> 	Has anyone tried to fit a 10 x 890 ?





A wider belt would have to be longer to fit with the stock washers.  You
would have to add washers to make a 10x890 fit, if it would fit at all.  I
had to do this a few years ago when I couldn't find the proper 9.5x905
belt.  I learned my lesson and have carried a correct spare since.

George
